transformed cells. The results we present here highlight an unexpected possible 
outcome of cellular immortalization driven by telomerase reactivation, and 
indicate that, in some cases, an artificial extension of cellular replicative 
capacity can increase the probability of occurrence of genomic alterations, 
which can lead to cellular transformation.

